overview: >-
  The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was functional but lacked visual appeal.
  The agent initiated a comprehensive review of the app's styling, starting with
  global CSS and core UI components, then moving to individual sections.

  The approach involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigning the main form layout with subtle background elements and an
  improved progress indicator, and enhancing the welcome screen with feature
  cards. All 14 questionnaire sections were updated to ensure consistent
  styling, replacing generic gray boxes with more refined, themed card-style
  groupings and updating typography and interactive states for form fields like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. The report section also received a
  visual refresh.

  During the process, a console error related to  values being passed to
  input fields was identified and fixed by modifying the  component to
  safely handle  values. The outcome is a visually cohesive, professional,
  and calming sleep questionnaire app, with all identified aesthetic issues
  addressed and a critical console error resolved.
